Definitely worse than liquid memories. If you get it early in a run, it may have no valid targets at all, which can be rough against act 1 elites. Probably the most notable exhaust cards for hermit are golden bullet, cursed weapon, eye of the storm, gestalst, and snipe. You also have showdown and high caliber, but those are less useful. Gestalt can be really good to get back for blocking large single hits, eye of the storm can be a great play extender, and golden bullet and cursed weapon both provide burst damage. 

That does give it a decent bit of utility, but you need to actually have those cards for this to work, so it's a pretty weak potion for a rare. I would rarely buy this from a shop, and would look to use it sort of like a fire potion if I had access to any of the damage options. Exhaust cards of course go up in value a bit if this potion is dropped and you don't have access to any.
